                            <comment id="67502" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 02:57:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the simpler case above I recommend creating two methods. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For more optional template variables where the number of required methods would grow, as mentioned in the referenced article, you can now apply URI template variables to an object&apos;s properties via data binding (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6909&quot; title=&quot;Add support for data binding from URI template variables to JavaBeans&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-6909&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-6909&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
